 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
 
 The encoding issues don't seem like they'd be relevant to this symptom.
 
 When you say it works with 4.2.5, were you using the same machine
 (same keyboard, same OS, etc.)?
 
 Also, can you try running this from an command-line:
 
   racket -l tests/gracket/showkey
 
 and then hitting return and sending us the output?
 
 This is what I see when I do that on my mac, just so you get an idea:
 
 1 KEY: "\r" =3D ASCII 13
   rel-code: down
   other-codes: (#f #f #f #f)
   mods:
 2 KEY: release
   rel-code: "\r" =3D ASCII 13
   other-codes: (#f #f #f #f)
   mods:
 
 Also, if that command fails with an error saying that it cannot find
 "tests/gracket" then that means that you've got the standard
 distribution, not the full one, so you should be able take the
 attached file, save it somewhere, and then run "racket showkey.rkt" to
 get the same effect.
 
 Thanks,
 Robby
 
