 This is a multi-part message in MIME format.
 --------------050208000001020903090504
 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8; format=flowed
 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
 
 I could solve the issue:)
 As it turns out via xev, both keys, return and enter, work like enter 
 keys. I then loaded Win7 on my laptop and installed DrRacket 5.2. There, 
 expressions in the interactive window are evaluated by pressing both 
 keys, return /and/ enter. I then installed a windows-like xev and saw, 
 that return works like the enter key - so it is a hardware problem.
 After some googling I got the information, that on Acer laptops, return 
 works as an enter key, even if there is a number board. To get the 
 functionality of return, you have to press Fn + return/enter - and that 
 works perfectly well with DrRacket on Linux Mint:)
 
 Thank you both very much for your help, now I can go on working:)
 Cheers
 Daniel
 
