Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/12450: Interactive window does not work
Date: Mon, 19 Dec 2011 08:25:42 -0600

 I think I understand. (But my keyboard (and the gui libraries) call
 the one on the main keyboard "return" and the one on the numeric
 keypad (or accessible via modifiers on a laptop) "enter".)
 
 One additional wrinkle here is that (what I and the gui library) call
 "enter" is sometimes not accessible unless you are holding down a
 modifier key (e.g., on american mac laptop keyboard).
 
 So, how about this:
 
   return/enter: behavior 1 below
 
   c-return/c-enter: behavior 2 below
 
   s-return/s-enter: behavior 3 below (but with indentation).
 
 In all cases above, optionally allow "alt" (so alt-return is behavior
 1, alt-control-enter is behavior 2, etc) in case we're on a platform
 where "enter" is the same thing as pressing "alt return".
 
 Does that sound right?
 
 Robby
 
