 Ugh, I should have checked...  Yes, that's the opposite of the terms
 on my keyboard, and on any PC-like laptop I've used...  In any case,
 if they're both the same, then such confusions will no longer happen.
 
 
 > One additional wrinkle here is that (what I and the gui library)
 > call "enter" is sometimes not accessible unless you are holding down
 > a modifier key (e.g., on american mac laptop keyboard).
 
 Right -- and IMO that's a point in favor of making them be the same.
 (=> no special functionality on the keypad one, which is harder to get
 on laptops.)
 
 
 > So, how about this:
 > 
 >   return/enter: behavior 1 below
 > 
 >   c-return/c-enter: behavior 2 below
 > 
 >   s-return/s-enter: behavior 3 below (but with indentation).
 
